        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 3:21PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mattituck, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Mattituck around 325 PM EDT.
Peconic around 330 PM EDT.
Southold around 340 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
